skills.skill: Knowledge of OSHA, FDA, and HIPAA compliance

duties_responsibilities.duty: Provide care to patients in various outpatient specialties while adhering to compliance standards.
Recognize patient needs and prioritize those needs with the needs outlined by physicians.
Assist in the management of patient care in the physician office setting under the direct supervision of a physician or licensed provider.
Demonstrate competency to provide patient care according to the specific needs of the population.

education_certification.credential: Must be a Registered Professional Nurse with current licensure. CPR, ACLS, and BCLS Certification. Knowledge of OSHA, FDA, and HIPAA compliance.
